'''Ramón M. López''' is the incumbent [[Secretary of Trade and Industry (Philippines)|Secretary of Trade and Industry]] under the [[Rodrigo Duterte]]'s administration. Before he was appointed as the DTI secretary, he was the Vice President and Executive Assistant to the President and CEO of [[RFM Corporation]],<ref>{{cite news|url=http://foodevolution.com.ph/2016/06/ramon-lopez-formally-resigns-from-rfm-to-head-dti/|title=Ramon Lopez formally resigns from RFM to head DTI|publisher=Food Evolution|accessdate=July 7, 2016}}</ref> having served for the company for 22 years, and Executive Director of Go Negosyo of the Philippine Center for Entrepreneurship.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://news.abs-cbn.com/nation/06/13/16/duterte-names-dti-dot-doh-chiefs|title=Duterte names DTI, DOT, DOH chiefs|publisher=[[ABS-CBN News]]|date=June 13, 2016|accessdate=July 7, 2016}}</ref>

He topped his Master in Development Economics at [[Williams College]] in [[Massachusetts]] (1988) and finished his AB Economics degree at the [[University of the Philippines Diliman]] in 1981.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://tpb.gov.ph/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/RAMON-LOPEZ.pdf|title=Hon. Ramon M. Lopez JR. Secretary Department of Trade and Industry (DTI)  Resume|last=|first=|date=|website=|publisher=|access-date=December 6, 2016}}</ref>

