'''Ransomes Industrial Estate''', also known as '''Ransomes Europark''' is combined [[retail park|retail]] and [[business park]] on the South-Eastern edge of [[Ipswich]] in [[Suffolk]], [[United Kingdom|UK]]. It takes its name from [[Ransomes, Sims & Jefferies]], which still maintains a presence on the park.

Predominantly the park consists of [[light industry|light industrial]] and [[logistics]] companies, although there is a growing number of [[retail]]ers and [[office]]s including the head office for [[KDM International]] and [[Mediterranean Shipping Company|MSC UK]].

{{As of|2008|02|alt=In February 2008}} it was announced that [[IKEA]] are in talks to take on part of the estate occupied by [[Crane Fluid Systems]] for a new store.<ref>{{cite news|publisher=East Anglian Daily Times|url=http://www.eadt.co.uk/search/story.aspx?brand=EADOnline&category=News&itemid=IPED28%20Feb%202008%2023:53:15:577&tBrand=EADOnline&tCategory=search|title=Ikea 'in talks' to create Ipswich store|date=29 February 2008|accessdate=2008-03-04}} {{Dead link|date=October 2010|bot=H3llBot}}</ref>

